1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 321, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 321. A. The following sales are hereby exempted from
4 the stamp excise tax levied pursuant to the provisions of Section
5 301 et seq. of this title:
6 1. All cigarettes sold to veterans hospitals and state operated
7 domiciliary homes for veterans located in the State of Oklahoma this
8 state, for distribution or sale to disabled ex-servicemen or
9 disabled ex-servicewomen interned in, or inmates of, such hospitals,
10 or residents of such homes;
11 2. All sales to the United States; and
12 3. All sales to a federally recognized Indian tribe or nation
13 which has entered into a compact with the State of Oklahoma this
14 state pursuant to the provisions of subsection C of Section 1 of
15 this act 346 of this title or to a licensee of such a tribe or
16 nation, upon which the payment in lieu of taxes required by the
17 compact has been paid; and
18 4. All sales to a federally recognized Indian tribe or nation
19 or to a licensee of such a tribe or nation upon which the tax levied
20 pursuant to the provisions of Section 4 of this act has been paid.
21 B. An exemption is hereby provided for the sale of cigarettes
22 that are intended to be heated rather than burned equal to fifty
23 percent (50%) of the taxes levied pursuant to the provisions of
24 Section 301 et seq. of this title.
